    lore: "**Qui-Gon Jinn** was a Jedi Master of great wisdom and power, but one who often found himself at odds with the Jedi High Council. Known as a 'maverick,' he prioritized the 'Living Force'—the immediate, present energy of all things—over the rigid prophecies and political concerns of the Order. It was this unique perspective that led him to discover the young **Anakin Skywalker** on Tatooine and believe him to be the 'Chosen One' who would bring balance to the Force.\n\nA master of Form IV (Ataru), Qui-Gon's combat style was aggressive and physical, utilizing the Force to augment his strength and speed. He was the first Jedi in centuries to rediscover the secret of retaining one's consciousness after death, eventually becoming the first Force Ghost. His death at the hands of Darth Maul was a turning point for the galaxy, as it deprived Anakin of the father figure he desperately needed. Qui-Gon was a man of deep compassion and insight, a Jedi who understood that the true path of the Force often lies outside the boundaries of tradition.",
    triviaInfo: "Origin: Born on Coruscant, he was the Padawan of Count Dooku. He first appeared in Star Wars: The Phantom Menace (1999).\n\nBattles: He fought in many missions for the Republic, but his most famous battle was the duel against Darth Maul on Naboo, where he fought alongside his apprentice Obi-Wan Kenobi.\n\nSpecial Abilities & Gear: He was a master of Ataru lightsaber combat and had a deep connection to the Living Force. He wielded a green-bladed lightsaber.\n\nSecret Trivia: Qui-Gon's name is derived from the Chinese 'Qigong,' a system of coordinated body-posture and movement, breathing, and meditation. He was the first Jedi shown to use a commlink in the films, which was actually a modified Gillette Women's Sensor Excel Razor.",
