    description: "A legendary figure who was both a Jedi hero and a Sith Lord.",
    lore: "**Revan** is one of the most complex and legendary figures in the history of the galaxy. Once a brilliant Jedi Knight who led the Republic to victory in the Mandalorian Wars, he eventually fell to the dark side and became the feared **Darth Revan**, the Dark Lord of the Sith. Following his defeat and the wiping of his memory by the Jedi Council, he was given a second chance, eventually rediscovering his identity and choosing to fight for the Light once again.\n\nA master of both the Light and Dark sides of the Force, Revan was a peerless strategist and a formidable warrior. He wielded two lightsabers—one violet and one crimson—symbolizing his unique path through the Force. He understood that true mastery requires the balance of both emotions and discipline. Revan's legacy is one of redemption and the idea that one's past does not define their future. He remains a figure of intense study and reverence for both Jedi and Sith alike, the man who stood at the center of the galactic wheel and refused to be broken by either side.",
    triviaInfo: "Origin: Revan's early origins are unknown, but he rose to prominence during the Old Republic era. He first appeared in the video game 'Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic' (2003).\n\nBattles: He defeated Mandalore the Ultimate to end the Mandalorian Wars and later led a massive Sith campaign against the Republic. He eventually saved the Republic from his own former apprentice, Darth Malak.\n\nSpecial Abilities & Gear: He is a master of many lightsaber forms and can seamlessly blend Light and Dark Force powers. He famously wears a Mandalorian mask he took during the wars.\n\nSecret Trivia: Revan's identity was the subject of one of the most famous plot twists in video game history. His character has been a fan favorite for decades, ultimately leading to his inclusion in modern Star Wars canon through various references. He is known as the 'Prodigal Knight'.",
