    universe: "Star Wars",
    description: "A protocol droid fluent in over six million forms of communication.",
    lore: "**C-3PO** is a golden-plated protocol droid who was built by a young **Anakin Skywalker** on the desert planet of Tatooine. Programmed for etiquette and protocol, he is fluent in over six million forms of communication, making him an invaluable—if often anxious—member of the Rebel Alliance and the Resistance. He is almost always accompanied by his best friend and counterpart, the astromech **R2-D2**.\n\nWhile he is not a warrior by nature, 3PO's vast knowledge of languages and galactic customs has helped the heroes navigate diplomatic crises and understand alien cultures. He is known for his constant worrying and his tendency to recite the odds of survival, a trait that often exasperates his more daring companions. Yet, despite his protocol, he has shown immense bravery in the face of danger, even sacrificing his own memory to help his friends. C-3PO is the heart of any diplomatic mission, a droid who proves that in a galaxy of war, the power of communication is just as vital as the power of a blaster.",
